=#000000 class=headings><font color=#A0B0E0>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#000000 class=headings><font color=#A0B0E0>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukosmaul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kosmaul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 6:28:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2836.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/gevry12/daoc/emblem WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Having Problems - part 2.</span><hr size=1> When I stick someone, even right from the front, I am finding that my PA is not landing properly lately. <br><br>Any others seeing this too ?<br><br> <p><table width="350" border="0"><tr><td width="144"><div align="center"><img src="http://www.geraldfield.com/nadinesplace/calvinquiz/stupendous.gif" width="142" height="125" align="absmiddle"></div></td><td><div align="center"><b><font size="3">You are Stupendous Man!</font></b><br><font size="2">You are simply amazing, whether you are battling your arch-nemesis Mom Lady, the nefarious Babysitter Girl, or the fiendish Annoying Girl. And you have absolutely nothing to do with mild-mannered Calvin.<br><font size="1">Take the <a href="http://www.geraldfield.com/cgi-bin/unofficial/quizzes/sfesurvey.cgi?whatcalvinareyou" target="_blank">What Calvin are You? Quiz</a> by <a href="mailto:contessina_2000@yahoo.com">contessina_2000@yahoo.com</a>!</font></font></div></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ripre>ripre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 7:29:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2836.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /stick and PA</span><hr size=1> Until recently I didn't use /stick until after I got off my PA and CD (when I've begun to melee).  I found that in RvR the people keep moving, so I would miss my CD, which is detrimental to my battle.  I decide to move my /stick macro to the same bar as my openning moves and made the following observation:<br><br>In this order, I will miss my CD almost everytime<br>1) target mob/invader<br>2) STICK<br>3) PA<br>4) PA misses, CD is started but useless.<br><br>I reordered the way I did this to:<br>1) target mob/invader<br>2) PA<br>3) STICK<br>4) PA hits, CD is started<br><br>You should be able to hit your PA, STICK, CD hotkeys all in a VERY quick succession, and it will almost always get your PA off successfully, with you immediately stuck to your target and the CD already queue'd up.  Hope that helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaureliuscov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurelius CoV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 8:34:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2836.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /stick and PA</span><hr size=1> I have noticed (and you may have also) that positional styles are really based on angles, rather than your actual stance to them.<br><br>IE: If someone runs at me at 180degrees and I am facing their direction at 360 degrees I dont have to actually be in front of them. If they are off to the side and the *angles* line up correctly *and* I am within strike range then I hit my PA. <br><br>You can test this out by lining up PAs in PVE from as far left/right as you can to see what I mean.<br><br>Once you /stick, you arent controlling the angle anymore which is why I also save that for right after the PA is hit.<br><br>Once I discovered this, it helped greatly in RvR especially in closelines. Trying to shimmy left and right to get in front of them is too hard, but now I know I only have to get close and line up the angles correctly.... <p><center><br>"I am still learning" <br>- Michelangelo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=drolk>Drolk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 10:44:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2836.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /stick and PA</span><hr size=1> I buy that too.  I hunt mobs in a duo all the time - the caster pulls from behind me, the mob runs toward us, I PA and get aggro for a round or two, then the caster unloads on it to help finish.<br><br>I've found consistently that PA is based on you being anywhere in front of the target, facing the plane of their approach.  Even if the mob is graphically a few steps either side of me, if I'm facing his approach and hit PA before he passes me, it'll go off 99% of the time.<br><br>I also don't touch stick until after PA goes off, but then I stick before the non-positional CD.  Best way to miss a PA is to stick first. <p>Drolk - L43 Kobold Shadowblade (Tristan)<BR><i>In the shadow of the valley of death, I walk alone.</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=drolk>Drolk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 10:47:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2836.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /stick and PA</span><hr size=1> Also, I believe that the way the mechanics work gives us a certain bonus to a PA attack while either the target or you are in motion.  Maybe it's a certain fudge they allow to help with lag-induced misses?<br><br>But very consistently, if you try PA while things are in motion it'll go off, while fiddling around already stuck to a target until things seem perfect and then hitting it will very often result in a failure. <p>Drolk - L43 Kobold Shadowblade (Tristan)<BR><i>In the shadow of the valley of death, I walk alone.</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uanimalmom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>animalmom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/18/02 11:05:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2836.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /stick and PA</span><hr size=1> Interesting, I find stick invaluable, especially when the target is moving, I /stick at max range and warp in with the strafe keys lining it up.<br><br>I almost never miss.  hmm <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=2836.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.sh